For many years I've preferred simple, understandable tools. Atua is my
personal Gopher server. It's written in Retro (my personal Forth
dialect), and provides a very basic Gopher server running via inetd or
tcpserver.

There is also Atua-WWW, a variant of Atua that uses HTTP to talk
to standard browsers. (This also translates the gophermaps to HTML).

